          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1702394672876-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potato[e]s</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394688819-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394688819-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394688819-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394688819-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1702394688819-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394683185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394683185-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394683185-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394683185-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1702394683185-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>grated garlic</strong> to the pot with the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>and<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>to the pot with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 22-25 min or until the potatoes are tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702394697243-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702394697243-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702394697243-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702394697243-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1702394697243-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>On a separate board, chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large-bite sized pieces</p><p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702394701458-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702394701458-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702394701458-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702394701458-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1702394701458-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, add the <strong>chopped basa </strong>to the pot with the <strong>drained king prawns</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce to medium and cook for 4-5 min, stirring occasionally, or until the fish and prawns are cooked through – this is your <strong>bouillabaisse-style basa & king prawn stew</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702394705206-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702394705206-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702394705206-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702394705206-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1702394705206-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through, then spread with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Cut each buttered half into triangles – this is your<strong> buttery ciabatta</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702394709314-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702394709314-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702394709314-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702394709314-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1702394709314-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bouillabaisse-style basa & king prawn stew</strong> in bowls with the <strong>buttery ciabatta</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
